<div class="arial8"><i>Thu, 08 Mar 2018 08:17:42</i></div><div id="post" class="panel">
          <div class="arial13"><b>Giant Days #36 is in the world!</b></div><span class="panel"><figure class="tmblr-full" data-orig-height="1528" data-orig-width="994"><img src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/e52141ae5c51ff322eb49590644fd1cd/tumblr_inline_p59iv9H9PQ1qfkyq6_540.jpg" data-orig-height="1528" data-orig-width="994"/></figure><p>Giant Days 36 is out and I can assure you, it’s guaranteed to please. Available in comic shops and <a href="https://www.comixology.co.uk/Giant-Days-36/digital-comic/630248">via Comixology</a>. Written by me, drawn by MAX SARIN, coloured by WHITNEY COGAR and lettered by JIM CAMPBELL. A must!</p></span><br />
          </div><div class="arial8"><i>Tue, 06 Mar 2018 19:06:39</i></div><div id="post" class="panel">
          <div class="arial13"><b>Shut Up About Bitcoin shirt</b></div><span class="panel"><figure class="tmblr-full" data-orig-height="1000" data-orig-width="1000"><img src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/2afa4e7effe30b1052e85d2001fb3793/tumblr_inline_p56nqdCLUv1qfkyq6_540.jpg" data-orig-height="1000" data-orig-width="1000"/></figure><p>To celebrate several years of not designing a t-shirt, I have designed a t-shirt! It’s for everyone who is tired of “cryptocurrency” chat. Which I reckon is almost everybody in the world so we’re gonna sell billions of them, maybe invest heavily while the getting is good!.</p><p><a href="https://topatoco.com/collections/scary-go-round/products/sgr-shutupbitcoin">On sale here - along with many other fine Scary Go Round products. </a></p></span><br />
          </div><div class="arial8"><i>Sat, 03 Mar 2018 17:40:42</i></div><div id="post" class="panel">
          <div class="arial13"><b>A new broom</b></div><span class="panel"><p>My cartoon kingdom is always in a varying state of disarray, but I’ve spent today trying to tidy up my mess. Now that Bad Machinery is complete, I’ve put all 10 cases, plus <i>Space IsThe Place</i> and <i>The Big Hiatus</i>, in <a href="http://scarygoround.com/badmachinery/ar.php">their own sub-site</a>, where you can read them end to end without interruption from weird side-stories and fill-ins.</p><p>Fans of weird side stories and fill-ins, fear not. <a href="http://scarygoround.com/bobbins/chapters.php">The New Bobbins archive</a> now positively bulges with everything that I’ve done with the wider universe from 2013 to 2017, with a new story guide and everything. The epic <i>longeurs</i>, the birth stories, the flagrant fan-service, the Desmond Fishmans - all there.</p><p>And Bobbins.horse may have lost its domain, but you can <a href="http://bobbins.badmachinery.com">still read it here</a>. I’ve also updated the <a href="http://scarygoround.com/newreader.php">NEW READER GUIDE</a> so you can navigate all the other backwaters of my work.</p><p>So I guess the question now is, what is the future for Scary Go Round? A lot of comics and books came out with my name on them over the last couple of years, so I’m trying to steer clear of self-publishing for a while. As a result, I’ve made a lot of comics that probably aren’t going to be printed anywhere, they’ll just exist here. </p><p> I’ve cleared out the main archive on the site to contain only comics from the start of 2018, this weird new era. While I’m working on the monthly Giant Days book (and another, soon-to-be-announced project), format and schedule will ebb and flow a bit more than usual, but I’m pleased to still be here and I’m glad you are too.</p></span><br />
          </div></div>
